cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a new model for time series data that uses ODEs to handle non-uniform intervals between observations. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given that the paper focuses on the performance of the model on irregularly-sampled data, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE. However, the use of ODEs may also make it relevant to cs.SY and cs.CV.
